if you were to program in JS in a style which calls for passing operations around you would have the operator `+` wrapped, so the second version would probably look like this<p><pre><code>    var sum = range(100).reduce(0, plus);
</code></pre>
or rather<p><pre><code>    var total = sum(range(100));
</code></pre>
this does not take away from the beauty of APL.

You can add your own exceptions if you want. Just have all your messages like:<p><pre><code>    message FooResult {

      optional Exception exception = 1;
      optional Foo foo = 2;
    }</code></pre>
